00:53:38.370 --> 00:53:40.380
Is that something
inherent to foxes

00:53:40.380 --> 00:53:43.350
or how quickly they
reproduce or to some larger

00:53:43.350 --> 00:53:46.120
classification of animals than,
like, if you selected something

00:53:46.120 --> 00:53:49.320
from a totally different,
not related at all

00:53:49.320 --> 00:53:50.490
to foxes or wolves--

00:53:50.490 --> 00:53:51.720
what would that be?

00:53:51.720 --> 00:53:53.720
LEE ALLEN DUGATKIN: Yeah,
it's a great question.

00:53:55.290 --> 00:53:58.290
And we know the
answer to some extent

00:53:58.290 --> 00:54:03.650
because, on the other side of
the farm where the foxes are,

00:54:03.650 --> 00:54:06.180
are hundreds and
hundreds of mink.

00:54:06.180 --> 00:54:09.540
And for the last 40
years, another person

00:54:09.540 --> 00:54:13.920
has been running the exact
same protocol on mink

00:54:13.920 --> 00:54:18.010
and finding very
parallel results.

00:54:18.010 --> 00:54:22.230
So they're smaller animals, so
they're not quite as dramatic

00:54:22.230 --> 00:54:23.850
and sexy as what
happens in the foxes,

00:54:23.850 --> 00:54:26.590
but if you choose on
behavior and behavior alone--

00:54:26.590 --> 00:54:29.610
and they've done that both
domesticated and aggressive

00:54:29.610 --> 00:54:30.990
like with the foxes--

00:54:30.990 --> 00:54:33.100
you not only get
behavioral changes,

00:54:33.100 --> 00:54:35.160
but you get changes
in coat coloration,

00:54:35.160 --> 00:54:38.800
hormone levels, juvenilized
